definition.value: An organic disodium salt having 2-(3-{2-tert-butyl-7-[ethyl(3-sulfonatopropyl)amino]chromenium-4-yl}prop-2-en-1-ylidene)-3-(3-carboxypropyl)-3-methyl-1-(3-sulfonatopropyl)indoline-5-sulfonate as the counterion.

An organic trisodium salt having 2-(3-{7-[bis(3-sulfonatopropyl)amino]-2-tert-butylchromenium-4-yl}prop-2-en-1-ylidene)-1-(3-carboxypropyl)-3-methyl-3-(3-sulfonatopropyl)indoline-5-sulfonate as the counterion.

A member of the class of oxazolidines that is 1,3-oxazolidin-2-one in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by an N-{[(5-nitro-2-furyl)methylene]amino} group. It has antibacterial and antiprotozoal properties, and is used in the treatment of giardiasis and cholera.
A member of the class of chalcones that is isoliquiritigenin in which one of the hydroxy groups at position 2' is replaced by a methoxy group.

An organic disodium salt having 2-{3-[2-tert-butyl-6,8,8-trimethyl-9-(3-sulfonatopropyl)-8,9-dihydropyrano[3,2-g]quinolin-1-ium-4-yl]prop-2-en-1-ylidene}-3-(3-carboxypropyl)-3-methyl-1-(3-sulfonatopropyl)indoline-5-sulfonate as the counterion.
A disaccharide derivative that is beta-D-apiofuranosyl-(1->6)-D-glucopyranose with a 4-(prop-2-en-1-yl)phenyl group substituent.
A C5n terpene, where n is greater than 8.

Any terpenoid derived from a sesquarterpene. The term includes compounds in which the C35 skeleton of the parent sesquarterpene has been rearranged or modified by the removal of one or more skeletal atoms (generally methyl groups).
A triterpenoid based on a  hopane skeleton.

An organic disodium salt having 3-(3-carboxypropyl)-3-methyl-1-(3-sulfonatopropyl)-2-{3-[6,8,8-trimethyl-2-phenyl-9-(3-sulfonatopropyl)-8,9-dihydropyrano[3,2-g]quinolin-1-ium-4-yl]prop-2-en-1-ylidene}indoline-5-sulfonate as the counterion.

An organic trisodium salt having 3-(3-carboxypropyl)-2-{3-[8,8-dimethyl-2-phenyl-6-(sulfonatomethyl)-9-(3-sulfonatopropyl)-8,9-dihydropyrano[3,2-g]quinolin-1-ium-4-yl]prop-2-en-1-ylidene}-3-methyl-1-(3-sulfonatopropyl)indoline-5-sulfonate as the counterion.

An organic trisodium salt having 2-(3-{4-tert-butyl-7-[ethyl(3-sulfonatopropyl)amino]chromenium-2-yl}prop-2-en-1-ylidene)-3-(3-carboxypropyl)-3-methyl-1-(3-sulfonatopropyl)indoline-5-sulfonate as the counterion.
Neutral molecules having charge-separated forms with an oxonium atom which bears no hydrogen atoms and that is not adjacent to the anionic atom.

An organic disodium salt having 2-(5-{2-tert-butyl-7-[ethyl(3-sulfonatopropyl)amino]chromenium-4-yl}penta-2,4-dien-1-ylidene)-3-(3-carboxypropyl)-3-methyl-1-(3-sulfonatopropyl)indoline-5-sulfonate as the counterion.

An organic trisodium salt having 2-(5-{7-[bis(3-sulfonatopropyl)amino]-2-tert-butylchromenium-4-yl}penta-2,4-dien-1-ylidene)-3-(3-carboxypropyl)-3-methyl-1-(3-sulfonatopropyl)indoline-5-sulfonate as the counterion.
An octadecatrienoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of alpha-linolenic acid.

An organic monosodium salt that has 3-(3-carboxypropyl)-2-[5-(9-ethyl-6,8,8-trimethyl-2-phenyl-8,9-dihydropyrano[3,2-g]quinolin-1-ium-4-yl)penta-2,4-dien-1-ylidene]-3-methyl-1-(3-sulfonatopropyl)indoline-5-sulfonate as the counterion.
An organic chloride salt comprising of a tetrabutylammonium cation and chloride anion.
